    "description": "The Daito Bank, Ltd. provides various banking products and services to individual and corporate customers in Japan. It operates through Banking, Leasing Business, and Other segments. The company accepts yen, fixed, savings, and foreign currency deposits; and offers financial products, intermediary business, and government bonds. It also provides housing, car, education, reform, card, free, and expansion and renovation loans; and pension and insurance, as well as financial product brokerage, investment trust, web account transfer reception, online payment/electronic money charge, and pay-easy fund transfer acceptance services. In addition, the company offers cash, credit and debit cards, safe-deposit boxes, and credit guarantees, as well as foreign currency, automatic money transfer, ATM, and Internet banking services. The company was formerly known as Daito Mutual Bank and changed its name to The Daito Bank, Ltd. in 1989. The Daito Bank, Ltd. was incorporated in 1942 and is headquartered in Koriyama, Japan."
